other method:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
On the role API feature, create a logstash_writer role:

POST _security/role/logstash_writer
{
  "cluster": ["manage_index_templates", "monitor", "manage_ilm"], 
  "indices": [
    {
      "names": [ "logstash-*" ], 
      "privileges": ["write","create","create_index","manage","manage_ilm"]  
    }
  ]
}

*in our case, we have 2 indices logstash-* and zabbix-*, so we modify this line :
"names": [ "logstash-*" , "zabbix-*" ], 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Create a logstash_internal user and assign it the logstash_writer role:

POST _security/user/logstash_internal
{
  "password" : "x-pack-test-password",
  "roles" : [ "logstash_writer"],
  "full_name" : "Internal Logstash User"
}

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Configure Logstash to authenticate as the logstash_internal user and enabling TLS/SSL Encryption:

input {
  elasticsearch {
    ...
    user => logstash_internal
    password => x-pack-test-password
  }
}
filter {
  elasticsearch {
    ...
    user => logstash_internal
    password => x-pack-test-password

  }
}
output {
  elasticsearch {
    ...
    user => logstash_internal
    password => x-pack-test-password
    ssl_enabled => true
    ssl_certificate_authorities => '/path/to/cert.pem'
  }
}
